ZCZC OE64
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 152300 UTC
THIS PERIOD SHOULD START WITH A 998 LOW IN THE VICINITY OF SCOTLAND LEAVING
A HIGH OVER SERN UK WHILE A MAJOR 990 LOW OCCUPIES THE MID-ATLANTIC W OF
FRANCE AT THE SAME TIME. THE INITIAL LOW SHOULD SOON LOSE ITS IDENTITY THROUGH
TUESDAY WITH THE RIDGE AMPLIFYING TO MEET WITH A HIGH OVER ICELAND. THIS
HIGH SHOULD THEN BE DISPLACED NWARDS MIDWEEK AS THE ATLANTIC LOW 979 ERODES
ITS INFLUENCE IN THE SW APPROACHES. THE ATLANTIC LOW SHOULD THEN MAKE UNCERTAIN
ERRATIC EWARD PROGRESS LATER IN THE WORKING WEEK. THERE IS A RISK OF GALES
IN CENTRAL PORTPATRICK FM MONDAY WITH THIS SWATHE TRANSFERRING N AND E AND
EASING THROUGH TUESDAY. A NEW AREA OF PERIODIC GALES OR SEV GALES SHOULD
THEN SPREAD BODILY NE INTO SERN PORTPATRICK THROUGH TUESDAY PROBABLY CONTINUING
FOR THE REMAINDER OF THE PERIOD PERHAPS ADVANICNG TO SURVIVE AS A WEAKEND
SWATHE OF OCCASIONAL STRG WINDS OR NEAR GALES FOR NERN PORTPATRICK AFTER
MIDWEEK
